This paper is about applying data mining techniques to improve the performance of intrusion detection systems. It involves evaluating a comprehensive set of classifier algorithms using a well-known dataset (KDD99) and proposing two classifier algorithm selection models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
